 compute capital gains in case of slump sale;
 determine the quantum of exemption available on investment of capital gains/ net
consideration arising on transfer of certain assets and appreciate the conditions to be satisfied
to avail such exemption;
 compute the capital gains chargeable to tax applying the charging and deeming provisions
and giving effect to the exemptions available in respect of capital gains;
 identify the cases where an Assessing Officer can make a reference to the Valuation Officer;
 appreciate the concessional tax treatment available for short-term capital gains and for long
term capital gains on transfer of listed equity shares/ units of an equity oriented fund/ units of
a business trust;
